{
  "texts": [
    "We call the solution to this problem b w lasso.",
    "Note that, we constrain the problem to positive weight values (b w lasso s ≥ 0 for every s).",
    "The regression problems are solved for all the foreground pixels (jjyjj 2 > 0:25) individually.",
    "For every barcode i, we can construct an image with the estimated weight values as pixels: 0 for background and rejected pixels, and non-zero values from b w. We call these images weight maps.",
    "Figure 1f shows weight maps constructed with b w lasso which have not been filtered."
  ]
}